{{Navigate|Book=Grsecurity/Appendix|Curr=Subject Modes|Next=Subject Attributes|Prev=Role Attributes}}
{| style="border-collapse:collapse;border-bottom:3px solid #999;" cellpadding="3px" width=100% |-style="background:#666;color:white;" ! width=60px style="border:1px solid gray;" |Mode ! style="border:1px solid gray;text-align:left;" |Meaning |- |-style="background:lightgrey;" | style="border:1px solid gray;text-align:center;"|'''a''' | style="border:1px solid gray;"|Allow this process to talk to the ''/dev/grsec'' device. |- | style="border:1px solid gray;text-align:center;"|'''b''' | style="border:1px solid gray;"|Enable process accounting for processes in this subject. |-style="background:lightgrey;" | style="border:1px solid gray;text-align:center;"|'''d''' | style="border:1px solid gray;"|Protect the ''/proc/<pid>/fd'', ''/proc/<pid>/mem'', ''/proc/<pid>/cmdline'', and ''/proc/<pid>/environ'' entries for processes in this subject, |- | style="border:1px solid gray;text-align:center;"|'''h''' | style="border:1px solid gray;"|This process is hidden and only viewable by processes with the ''v'' mode. |-style="background:lightgrey;" | style="border:1px solid gray;text-align:center;"|'''i''' | style="border:1px solid gray;"|Enable inheritance-based learning, causing all accesses of this subject and anything it executes to be logged as originating from this subject. The policy generated from this learning will have the inheritance flag added to every file executed from this subject. |- | style="border:1px solid gray;text-align:center;"|'''k''' | style="border:1px solid gray;"|This process can kill protected processes. |-style="background:lightgrey;" | style="border:1px solid gray;text-align:center;"|'''l''' | style="border:1px solid gray;"|Enables learning mode for this process. |- | style="border:1px solid gray;text-align:center;"|'''o''' | style="border:1px solid gray;"|Override ACL inheritance for this process. |-style="background:lightgrey;" | style="border:1px solid gray;text-align:center;"|'''p''' | style="border:1px solid gray;"|This process is protected; it can only be killed by processes with the ''k'' mode, or by processes within the same subject. |- | style="border:1px solid gray;text-align:center;"|'''r''' | style="border:1px solid gray;"|Relax <tt>ptrace</tt> restrictions (allows <tt>ptracing</tt> of processes other than one's own children). |-style="background:lightgrey;" | style="border:1px solid gray;text-align:center;"|'''s''' | style="border:1px solid gray;"|(In v2.2.1 and above): Enable <tt>AT_SECURE</tt> when entering this subject. This enables the same environment sanitization that occurs in glibc upon execution of a suid binary. |- | style="border:1px solid gray;text-align:center;"|'''t''' | style="border:1px solid gray;"|Allow <tt>ptracing</tt> of any process (do not use unless necessary, allows <tt>ptrace</tt> to cross subject boundaries). This flag also allows a process to use <tt>CLONE_FS</tt> and execute a binary that causes a subject change. |-style="background:lightgrey;" | style="border:1px solid gray;text-align:center;"|'''v''' | style="border:1px solid gray;"|This process can view hidden processes. |- | style="border:1px solid gray;text-align:center;"|'''x''' | style="border:1px solid gray;"|Allows executable anonymous shared memory for this subject. |-style="background:lightgrey;" | style="border:1px solid gray;text-align:center;"|'''A''' | style="border:1px solid gray;"|Protect the shared memory of this subject. No other processes but processes contained within this subject may access the shared memory of this subject. |- | style="border:1px solid gray;text-align:center;"|'''C''' | style="border:1px solid gray;"|Auto-kill all processes belonging to the attacker's IP address upon violation of security policy. |-style="background:lightgrey;" | style="border:1px solid gray;text-align:center;"|'''K''' | style="border:1px solid gray;"|When processes belonging to this subject generate an alert, kill the process. |- | style="border:1px solid gray;text-align:center;"|'''O''' | style="border:1px solid gray;"|Allow loading of writable libraries. |-style="background:lightgrey;" | style="border:1px solid gray;text-align:center;"|'''T''' | style="border:1px solid gray;"|Deny execution of binaries or scripts that are writable by any other subject in the policy. This flag is evaluated at policy enable time. All binaries with execute permission that are writable by another subject (ignoring special roles) will be reported and the RBAC system will not allow itself to be enabled until the changes are made. |}
